Hello teams, Does anyone know how to create a Pipeline Detector for our Limelight 3?
We downloaded the Neural Networks from the official Limelight website, however, we wanted to make our own Detector Pipeline. We followed the steps in the official documentation, but the Google Colab Notebook doesn’t allow us to proceed from step 3. “Training Configuration and Labels File Generation”, onwards; and we don’t know why.
We use LimeLight 3 and Google Coral, btw.
Thanks in advance

So, right now the Colab notebook appears to be depreciated and incompatible with the latest version of Roboflow. A quick fix I found would be to install an older version of protobuf (3.20.3 was the one I used).

So just run this command in the front of the project:
!pip install protobuf==3.20.3

I’m pretty sure you’ll have to do this for every session of Colab you load up.
